$Id$

Build system
~~~~~~~~~~~~

Despotify is using the build system waf.
More info about waf can be found on: http://code.google.com/p/waf/


Dependencies
~~~~~~~~~~~~

You'll need:

Python >= 2.3.x (for the build system)
OpenSSL, zlib, libvorbis and expat (for the library)
ncurses or ncursesw (for the ncurses client)

Supported audio outputs are: CoreAudio, GStreamer, libao and PulseAudio

You need the -dev packages for all libraries except Python.


Configure
~~~~~~~~~

$ ./waf configure


Some options (see a more complete list with ./waf configure --help):
  --prefix=<path> : tells waf to put the installation in path
  --nocache : rerun all configuration tests.

  --debug : enables debug code
  --audio-output=<plugin> : selects this audio output plugin instead of autodetecting.
                            valid plugins: coreaudio, gstreamer, libao, pulseaudio


Building
~~~~~~~~

$ ./waf build

or just

$ ./waf


Some options (see a more complete list with ./waf build --help):
  -p : show a useless but cool progress bar when building!
  -j<num> : run <num> simultaneous compile processes, can speed up building


Installing
~~~~~~~~~~

$ sudo ./waf install


Running
~~~~~~~

Now you can run our ncurses client with

$ despotify <login> <password>

or the gateway

$ despotify-gateway <bind address> <bind port>


Tip for developers
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

If you don't want to install everytime you change something you can
set LD_LIBRARY_PATH to _build_/default/lib in your shell and then
run for example: _build_/default/clients/despotify/despotify
